        "goal_understanding": "The game's goal was to navigate a grid-based puzzle, completing each level by matching the player's piece attributes (shape, color, rotation) to the requirements of goal cells and then stepping onto those goal cells. Progress through all levels to win the game, while managing stamina and lives to avoid a game over.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "Each move costs 1 stamina. When stamina reaches 0, a life is lost and stamina resets to its maximum. Losing all lives ends the game. Walls block movement, and the game provides 'blocked_directions' to indicate impassable directions. Modifier tiles alter the piece's attributes: shape modifiers cycle through six shapes; color modifiers cycle through four colors (orange \u2192 blue \u2192 green \u2192 red \u2192 orange); rotation modifiers rotate 90\u00b0 clockwise (0\u00b0 \u2192 90\u00b0 \u2192 180\u00b0 \u2192 270\u00b0 \u2192 0\u00b0). A goal cell activates only when the carried piece's shape, color, and rotation all match its required values. Stepping onto an active goal completes it. All goals in a level must be completed to advance. Efficient route planning is essential due to limited turns."
